When
\fB$MSVC_NOTFOUND_POLICY\fR
is not specified, the default
\fBscons\fR
behavior is to issue a warning and continue subject to the conditions listed above\&. The default
\fBscons\fR
behavior may change in the future\&.
.sp
\fINew in version 4\&.4\fR
.RE
.PP
\fBMSVC_SCRIPT_ARGS\fR
.RS 4
Pass user\-defined arguments to the Visual C++ batch file determined via autodetection\&.
.sp

